'''Gonzalo Roberto Valle Bustamante''' (born 28 February 1996) is an Ecuadorian professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] side [[L.D.U. Quito]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzalo Valle|accessdate=10 January 2025|website=Soccerway|url= https://uk.soccerway.com/players/gonzalo-roberto-valle-bustamante/393830/}}</ref>

==Club career==
From [[Riobamba]], he joined [[Guayaquil City F.C.|Guayaquil City]] in 2014, making his first-team debut in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|website=Footboom1.com|date=6 June 2025|accessdate=6 June 2025|url= https://www.footboom1.com/en/news/football/2599741-who-is-gonzalo-valle-ecuador-s-goalkeeper-shining-against-brazil|title= Who Is Gonzalo Valle? Ecuador’s Goalkeeper Shining Against Brazil}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-porteros-alfaro-entrenamiento-gonzalo-valle.html#|website=elcomercio|accessdate=10 January 2025|title=Gustavo Alfaro calls up goalkeeper Gonzalo Valle for training with Ecuador|date=10 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Gonzalo Valle, el golero con sueños de grandeza del Guayaquil City|url= https://lacancha.movix.com/gonzalo-valle-el-golero-con-suenos-de-grandeza-del-guayaquil-city/|website=lacancha.movix.com|date=16 September 2022|accessdate=10 January 2025}}</ref> He featured for the club in the [[Copa Sudamericana]] for the first time in March 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/03/18/south-america/copa-sudamericana/sociedad-deportiva-aucas/cd-river-plate-ecuador/3455806/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=10 January 2025|title= AUCAS VS. GUAYAQUIL CITY 2 - 1|date=18 March 2021}}</ref> He joined [[L.D.U. Quito]] in January 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.ecuagol.com/noticias/ligapro/nuevo-guardian--liga-de-quito-anuncio-la-contratacion-de-gonzalo-valle/202850/| last= Beltrán |first=Bolívar |date=January 12, 2024|title=Liga de Quito announced the signing of Gonzalo Valle|website=ecuagol.com|accessdate=January 10, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|website=Studio Futbol|url= https://studiofutbol.com.ec/2024/01/12/oficial-ldu-confirmo-el-fichaje-de-gonzalo-valle/|accessdate=10 January 2025|title= OFICIAL: LDU confirmó el fichaje de Gonzalo Valle|first=Jesus|last=Alencastro|date=12 January 2024}}</ref> He made his debut in the Copa Sudamericana for Quito on 15 August 2024 against [[Club Atlético Lanús]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2024/08/15/south-america/copa-sudamericana/liga-deportiva-universitaria-de-quito/ca-lanus/4360924/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=10 January 2024|date=15 August 2024|title= LDU QUITO VS. LANÚS 1 - 2}}</ref>

==International career==
He was called-up to train with the [[Ecuador national football team]] for the first time in August 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://studiofutbol.com.ec/2022/08/16/video-gonzalo-valle-estar-en-la-seleccion-es-un-sueno-que-he-tenido-desde-nino/|title= Gonzalo Valle: "Being in the national team is a dream I have had since I was a child" |website=Studio Futbol |accessdate=10 January 2025 |first=Adrien |last=Guilen |date= 17 August 2022}}</ref> He was called-up again in October 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://studiofutbol.com.ec/2024/10/04/noticia-banco-guayaquil-los-convocados-de-la-tri-para-los-partidos-ante-paraguay-y-uruguay/ |website=Studio Futbol |date=4 October 2024 |accessdate=10 January 2025 |title=Noticia Banco Guayaquil // Los convocados de La Tri para los partidos ante Paraguay y Uruguay |first=Juan |last=Palacios}}</ref> He made his debut for Ecuador, keeping a clean sheet, in a 0-0 draw in their [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] on 5 June 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20250606-brazil-held-in-ancelotti-debut-paraguay-move-closer-to-qualifying|website=France24.com|accessdate=6 June 2025|date=5 June 2025|title= Brazil held in Ancelotti debut, Paraguay move closer to qualifying}}</ref>

